# Tell coding agents to skip these files when building context.
# Support varies by tool:
#   - Aider reads:      .aiderignore  (same syntax as this file)
#   - OpenCode reads:    check current docs -- some versions honor .gitignore
#   - Claude Code:       does not currently support a dedicated ignore file;
#                        rely on the env-var approach + file permissions instead
#
# IMPORTANT: this is a courtesy signal, not a security boundary. An agent
# that runs arbitrary shell commands can still `cat` these files unless
# your OS file permissions or the env-var-only secret approach block it.

.env
.env.*
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
secrets/
config/secrets*
**/credentials.json
**/*_rsa
**/*_ed25519
